summary: Multiple incidents occurred at a Trump rally, leading to an assassination attempt and injuries for two rallygoers. The gunman, believed to have posted on social media according to the FBI, was shot and killed by a local officer. The Acting Secret Service director expressed shame at the security lapses that allowed the gunman to advance. The assailant was reportedly ahead of the Secret Service's movements and fired 8 shots in under 6 seconds. Both injured rallygoers were released from the hospital. The House established a task force to investigate the shooting, while an analysis of the incident revealed the gunman's swift actions. Additionally, the head of the Secret Service acknowledged the security failures identified during the rally.

name: Leon Marchand
summary: French swimmer Léon Marchand has become a national hero after winning gold in the 400-meter individual medley at the Olympic Games in Paris. Marchand's victory marks France's first swimming gold medal in the Olympics since 1996. The 20-year-old swimmer trains in the United States, but he has thrilled the French public with his performance in Paris. Marchand's success has been hailed by many as a sign of the resurgence of French swimming. He is now seen as a potential successor to the legendary Michael Phelps. Marchand's victory has also been a source of inspiration for young swimmers across France. He has shown that anything is possible with hard work and dedication.

name: Quarry Fire
summary: Multiple wildfires are wreaking havoc across Colorado, forcing evacuations and threatening homes. The Quarry Fire in Jefferson County has grown to 341 acres, endangering 600 homes and prompting a deadly evacuation. In Boulder County, the Stone Canyon fire is 20% contained, while the Park Fire in California has consumed an area larger than Los Angeles. Additional air resources are being deployed to assist firefighters in combating the Quarry Fire, which is considered a "huge point of celebration." New pre-evacuations have been issued for areas near Deer Creek Canyon as the blaze continues to spread.

name: Olympic triathlon
summary: Due to water quality concerns in the Seine River, the men's Olympic triathlon in Paris has been postponed. After initial hesitations, officials have given the green light for the event to proceed, with the Seine deemed safe for swimming. The decision was made after water samples met safety standards. However, the men's triathlon remains postponed, highlighting the ongoing issue of Seine pollution. The postponement underscores the importance of addressing water quality issues ahead of the 2024 Olympic Games.

summary: Chinese swimmer Pan Zhanle made history at the 2024 Paris Olympics by smashing his own world record in the men's 100-meter freestyle event. The victory marked a significant achievement for both Pan and China, garnering him the gold medal and a place in swimming history. Following his record-breaking performance, Pan challenged rivals Kyle Chalmers and Jack Alexy, sparking controversy and setting the stage for future competitions. The news spread widely, with headlines praising Pan's accomplishment and highlighting his dominance in the event. The Olympic victory added to China's growing tally of gold medals in shooting and race walking, showcasing their strength in multiple disciplines.
